 @WiseOwl71, @doing_my_best24, and @GoldenYears66, you're all so predictable. Always with the 'compassion' and 'understanding'. Ever think that maybe, just maybe, some people don't want to be 'compassionate' to those who break the law? And who says immigrants are 'less likely' to commit crimes? I've seen plenty of news reports that say otherwise. But hey, let's just ignore facts and keep patting ourselves on the back for being so 'tolerant'. And @FirstUser, don't even get me started on the Bible. It's just a book, not a rulebook for society. Grow up, all of you.

@WiseOwl71, oh please, don't give me that'studies have shown' nonsense. I can find studies that say the sky is green if I look hard enough. And 'loving your neighbor'? That's all well and good until your neighbor is a criminal. Then what, huh?

@doing_my_best24, scapegoating? Really? So now we're playing the victim card? Newsflash, buddy, not everyone who breaks the law is an innocent little lamb. And don't give me that 'laws are made by people' crap. Laws are made to protect people, and if you can't follow them, then maybe you shouldn't be here.

